      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 47
    },
    {
      "id": "sybil_7_listing_2",
      "firm_id": "sybil_7",
      "description": "Available is a mechanically sound 2004 Porsche 911 Carrera featuring the refined 3.6L M96 flat-six powerplant equipped with VarioCam Plus. This unit delivers linear power through a crisp G96 6-speed manual transaxle. The chassis remains taut, utilizing a MacPherson strut front and multi-link rear suspension geometry that retains its factory-spec damping characteristics. Critically, the IMS bearing has been addressed with a dual-row ceramic retrofit, and the rear main seal (RMS) shows no signs of weeping. The braking system features four-piston monobloc calipers with cross-drilled rotors, showing plenty of pad life. While the finish shows honest road wear consistent with its mileage, the aerodynamic undertray and structural rigidity are fully intact. A driver-focused example for the enthusiast who prioritizes kinematic excellence over a concours finish.",
      "price": 32500.0,
      "reputation": 0.3,
      "quality": "poor",
      "quality_value": 0.1,
      "timestep_posted": 47
    },
    {
